## Installation

### Prerequisites

- Python 3.9 or higher
- pip

### Clone the Repository

```bash
git clone https://github.com/EngrMuhammadYounas/CYBERGUARD-IDS.git
cd CYBERGUARD-IDS
```

### Install Dependencies

```bash
pip install -r requirements.txt
```

**Required packages:**

```
lightgbm>=3.3.5
scikit-learn>=1.2.2
pandas>=1.5.3
numpy>=1.24.3
matplotlib>=3.7.1
seaborn>=0.12.2
shap>=0.41.0
joblib>=1.2.0
pyarrow>=12.0.0
```

---

## Usage

### 1. Download the Dataset

- **Kaggle (cleaned, recommended):** [ekkykharismadhany/csecicids2018-cleaned](https://www.kaggle.com/datasets/ekkykharismadhany/csecicids2018-cleaned)
- **CIC original:** [https://www.unb.ca/cic/datasets/ids-2018.html](https://www.unb.ca/cic/datasets/ids-2018.html)

### 2. Preprocess

```bash
python layer1_preprocess.py --input /path/to/dataset --output layer1_output
```

### 3. Train Each Layer

```bash
python layer2_gatekeeper.py  --input layer1_output --output models/l2_gatekeeper.pkl
python layer3_forensics.py   --input layer1_output --output models/l3_forensics.pkl
python layer4_sentinel.py    --input layer1_output --output models/l4_sentinel.pkl
```

### 4. Run Inference on Live Traffic

```bash
python inference.py --input HULKATTACK.csv --output results/
```

### Interactive Exploration

The full training notebook is on Kaggle:

[![Kaggle](https://img.shields.io/badge/Kaggle-Notebook-blue.svg)](https://www.kaggle.com/code/engrsadeeda/fyp-intrusion-detection-system)

